Mr Carden has pointed out some minor cracking within his property and was concerned that a TPO would prevent the removal of the tree if it were causing subsidence. I have reassured Mr Carden that providing there is reasonable justification,  ie that the ash in the balance of probability is the cause of the damage  then sufficient works which may include removal, will be allowed.
